# 2️⃣ Terraform Deployment of Blob Storage

Infrastructure as Code for Blob Storage is usually done using **Terraform** with **Microsoft Azure** provider.

DevOps teams use Terraform to create:

* Storage accounts
* Blob containers
* Lifecycle policies
* Network rules
* RBAC

---

# Terraform Architecture

```
Terraform
   │
   │ Azure Provider
   │
Azure Storage Account
   │
Blob Container
   │
Lifecycle Policies
```

---

# Step 1 — Provider Configuration

```hcl
provider "azurerm" {
  features {}
}
```

---

# Step 2 — Resource Group

```hcl
resource "azurerm_resource_group" "rg" {
  name     = "devops-rg"
  location = "East US"
}
```

---

# Step 3 — Storage Account

```hcl
resource "azurerm_storage_account" "storage" {
  name                     = "devopsblobstore123"
  resource_group_name      = azurerm_resource_group.rg.name
  location                 = azurerm_resource_group.rg.location
  account_tier             = "Standard"
  account_replication_type = "LRS"

  allow_blob_public_access = false
}
```

---

# Step 4 — Blob Container

```hcl
resource "azurerm_storage_container" "container" {
  name                  = "logs"
  storage_account_name  = azurerm_storage_account.storage.name
  container_access_type = "private"
}
```

---

# Step 5 — Lifecycle Policy

```hcl
resource "azurerm_storage_management_policy" "policy" {
  storage_account_id = azurerm_storage_account.storage.id

  rule {
    name    = "log-retention"
    enabled = true

    filters {
      prefix_match = ["logs/"]
      blob_types   = ["blockBlob"]
    }

    actions {
      base_blob {
        tier_to_cool_after_days_since_modification_greater_than = 30
        tier_to_archive_after_days_since_modification_greater_than = 90
        delete_after_days_since_modification_greater_than = 365
      }
    }
  }
}
```

---

